\par This section describes each skill, including common uses and typical modifiers.
\par }{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \ul\insrsid15551003 Skill Description Format}{\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \insrsid15551003 
\par Skill Name ([KEY ABILITY]; TRAINED ONLY; ARMOR CHECK PENALTY; [CLASS NAME] ONLY)
\par The skill name line includes the following information:
\par Key Ability: The abbreviation of the ability whose modifier applies to the skill check. Exception: Speak Language has "None" listed as its key ability because the use of this skill does not require a check.
\par Trained Only: If "Trained Only" is included in the skill name line, the character mus
t have at least 1 rank in the skill to use it. If it is omitted, the skill can be used untrained (with a rank of 0). If any special notes apply to trained or untrained use, they are covered in the Special section (see below).
\par Armor Check Penalty: Apply any armor check penalty to skill checks for this skill.
\par [Class Name] Only: The skill is exclusive to a certain class or classes. No character not of these classes can take the skill. If omitted, the skill is not exclusive.
\par The skill name line is followed by a general description of what using the skill represents. After the description are three other types of information:
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\fcs1 \af0 \fcs0 \f3\fs20\insrsid15551003 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls1\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fcs1 
